    <!-- Chosen Palette: Slate & Amber -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, dashboard-style single-page application was designed to transform the linear report into an intuitive, exploratory experience. The structure is organized into four key sections: 1) A main dashboard for a high-level overview of the core financial paradox (growth vs. profitability). 2) A deep dive into the 'Growth Dilemma' (income statement analysis). 3) An analysis of 'The Debt Climb' (balance sheet and risk). 4) An interactive summary of 'Risks & Recommendations'. This non-linear, thematic structure was chosen because it allows users to quickly grasp the main story and then drill down into areas of interest, which is more effective for data exploration and understanding than a traditional report format. Navigation is facilitated by a sticky header, enabling seamless movement between analytical themes. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - KPI Cards (HTML/CSS): Goal: Inform. Method: Large, clear stats for immediate insight into key metrics like Revenue, Net Profit, and Debt. Interaction: None, purely informational. Justification: Provides a quick, high-impact summary.
        - Dual-Axis Bar/Line Chart (Chart.js): Goal: Compare/Relationships. Method: Compares Revenue Growth (bars) against Net Margin decline (line). Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: This is the most critical visualization as it instantly tells the core story of unprofitable growth.
        - Multi-Line Chart (Chart.js): Goal: Compare/Change. Method: Shows the trend of Gross, EBITDA, and Net margins over time. Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Clearly illustrates the erosion of profitability at different levels of the operation.
        - Stacked Area Chart (Chart.js): Goal: Organize/Compare. Method: Visualizes the composition of the Balance Sheet (Assets vs. Liabilities & Equity). Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Effectively demonstrates the shrinking equity base relative to the exploding debt, highlighting the increased leverage.
        - Bar Chart (Chart.js): Goal: Compare. Method: Tracks key leverage and liquidity ratios (Debt/EBITDA, Current Ratio). Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Provides a clear, quantitative view of the increasing financial risk.
        - Interactive Cards (HTML/CSS/JS): Goal: Organize/Inform. Method: Presents qualitative risks in clickable cards that reveal detailed text. Interaction: Click to expand/collapse. Justification: Breaks down complex text into digestible chunks, making it more engaging than a long wall of text.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
